The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks to classify surgical skills based on kinematic data, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for personalized feedback to support novice surgeons, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
